    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in MCH scheduler non-MBSFN subframe checking\n\n### Summary\nAdded missing NULL check in `check_nonMBSFN_sf()` function to prevent segmentation faults when `non_mbsfn_SubframeConfig` is not initialized. This fixes a crash that could occur during MCH scheduling when certain MBSFN configuration parameters are not set.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_mch.c`: Added NULL check in `check_nonMBSFN_sf()` function before accessing `cc->non_mbsfn_SubframeConfig` structure members.\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be reproduced by running the MCH scheduler with a configuration where `non_mbsfn_SubframeConfig` is NULL. This typically occurs in certain MBSFN deployment scenarios where non-MBSFN subframe allocation is not configured. The segmentation fault occurs at line 232 where `check_nonMBSFN_sf()` is called as part of the subframe scheduling decision logic:\n\n```c\nshifted_sf = check_nonMBSFN_sf(frameP,cc,subframeP)+check_CAS_sf(frameP,subframeP);\n```\n\nWithout the fix, this results in a segmentation fault when `check_nonMBSFN_sf()` attempts to access members of the NULL pointer. With the fix, the function safely returns 0 (indicating the subframe is not a non-MBSFN subframe) and scheduling continues normally.\n"
}